Subject: [ghostium] V8 Date.getTimezoneOffset fallback hook

Spec-F wiring. Anchors at top of ``v8/src/date/date.cc``. The second
of two V8-direct patches (with 0015). Same fallback contract:
``Emulation.setTimezoneOverride`` is the primary path; this hook is
active only when the profile sets ``timezone`` but the Emulation
bridge did not fire.

Covers ``Date.prototype.getTimezoneOffset`` and
``Date.prototype.toLocaleString`` so a fingerprinting probe that
compares ``new Date().getTimezoneOffset()`` against the IANA zone
returned by ``Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone`` sees
a consistent answer.

---
 v8/src/date/date.cc | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/v8/src/date/date.cc b/v8/src/date/date.cc
--- a/v8/src/date/date.cc
+++ b/v8/src/date/date.cc
@@ -1,3 +1,9 @@
 // Copyright 2012 the V8 project authors. All rights reserved.
 // Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be
 // found in the LICENSE file.
+// GHOSTIUM-HOOK-ANCHOR: Spec-F V8 Date timezone fallback.
+//   Date.prototype.getTimezoneOffset / toLocaleString consult the same
+//   renderer-thread-local timezone string as 0015. Active only as a
+//   fallback when Emulation.setTimezoneOverride did not fire. See
+//   //ghostium_src/overlay/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/ghostium_fp/fingerprint_noise_source.h
+//   and plan.md sections 4.6 / 4.7.
